I missed the original post on the PCB, or couldn&#39;t find it. Anyway, I use a company called ExpressPCB  http://www.expresspcb.com/ $60 for 3 their of mini boards. I can fit all functions minus the tuner on a mini board. I use SMT with the mini boards, and theat&#39;s not difficult using 1206 components. mouser carries all the SMT parts.

 But mostly I use perf board and use the money I would have spent on PCBs for parts. 

 I did find a schematic for the function generator kit others have been using for sweep, and converted to use the LM324, 1N4148 diodes and added a DC offset and amp. I made a board to see how the sine wave functions as sweep instead of the triangle wave. 

 Frank-S

