&gt; &gt; Yes, that board should work. If you have a single-sided board pattern, after
&gt; &gt; you&#39;ve developed the photoresist (or ironed on the toner, if you do it that
&gt; &gt; way) spray the other side of the board with spray paint and let dry. I like
&gt; &gt; to use the clear coat paint but it doesn&#39;t really matter.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; After you&#39;ve etched one side, clean the paint and the photoresist off (clean
&gt; &gt; both sides) with acetone, MEK, etc. Do this in a well-ventilated area! Then
&gt; &gt; drill your holes.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; If you are going to make a double-sided board, drill a few of the holes that
&gt; &gt; have common pads on both sides to orient the pattern on the other side and
&gt; &gt; repeat whatever method you use to put a resist on that side. After it&#39;s
&gt; &gt; developed/ironed on, spray the already etched side with paint and etch the
&gt; &gt; other side. Clean off the board and drill holes.
&gt; &gt; 
